      "writtenOn": "2017-11-13T23:02:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Right, we probably want to optimize for calls that don\u0027t have return values.\n\nHowever, even with this unoptimized version, I am not seeing an adverse effect. In effect, it\u0027s the same as if there is a global lock on all GL calls, with a little more copying and context switching. angle_indirect uses it, and has less jank, plus Mac Antutu Garden runs faster with this (and Antutu Garden has many GL API calls per frame compared to most apps).",
      "parentUuid": "2ead224d_015e4859",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 126,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 127,
        "endChar": 37
      },
      "revId": "02103cad4127c1cdb0b8f6ad1651d83724c7bc0a",
